I'd say that when Stalker crashed into the wall, it would have made a huge 
dent, and the continous shots would have probably broken through.

::Zardus/Bloodystrike/Reptilica::

Zardus looks over at Feline, raising an eyebrow. He didn't get compliments 
too often. He looks her over, his face once again serious.

"You're not too bad yourself," he says, his voice resuming its seriousness 
and deadly tone, "I imagine you'll be able to use your ... charm in this 
mission."
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Bloodystrike walks past the torture chambers, nearly crashing into Reptilica 
as his friend walks out. Reptilica looks at Bloodystrike.

"Were you sent to help me?"

Bloodystrike shakes his head.

"Good," Reptilica says, throwing a brush aside, "'Cause I'm done."

Bloodystrike chuckles. "What'd ya do, piss Zardus off."

"Shut up," Reptilica mutters, the two making their way toward the bridge. 
They enter, Reptilica glancing at the scanners, his face lighting up. "Hey! 
There's a pod a few clicks from here! Let's go!"

Reptilica runs out of the bridge, Bloodystrike following.
